author: @hannahdy9697
text:
Hello, let me introduce NCT's main vocalist Doyoung to everyone here :)

The talented and amazing singer that he is:
1. His performance on King of Masked Singers https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLptT-Koxq1ra3xWixuVjlgijHQZKJW4VC

2. All his OSTs, solo song, collabs, covers, stations, special projects, vocal compilation and pre-debut performances https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLO_Bn7ySaxWstBnlgiGKYXPmbk10taX1T

3. Fancams https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLcKTuMwiBpH0DEEAESzfSD2qWYqr6DU26 

For a glimpse of how amazing he is as a person and how passionate and dedicated he is as a singer you can watch these videos:
1. Short compilation of his personality. For newer ones you can look up for his fan accounts on Twitter https://youtu.be/a5gasT-haGc 
 
2. He prepared these KoMS stages while he was busy with tours, comebacks and flying in and out of the country https://youtu.be/bGLYLQDazjo

Doyoung also debuted as an actor with a short drama called Cafe Midnight (ì‹¬ì•¼ì¹´í˜) Season 3 'The Curious Stalker' last year. Check out the trailer here: https://youtu.be/giEF7Rbg6yo 

Later on, he made his first appearance as musical actor in the musical Marie Antoinette and received great praises from seniors of the industry as well as the audiences.

His Instagram: instagram.com/do0_nct

He is the first ever K-pop artist that I fully stan starting 2017 although I've been listening to K-pop music way longer than that. He is not only an amazing artist but also has beautiful heart and always does his absolute best to connect with his fans. I hope this short introduction will interest any of you to check him further. Please give this gem a lot of love and support! â¤ï¸

author: @Kammy_-ez8jx
text: I was watching Aespa's interview on Twitter and Giselle mentioned that she had no hopes for passing the SM Saturday audition because it is THAT prestigious and incredibly difficult to pass since Lee Sooman himself is the judge. Jungwoo was one of the hundreds of people on line one of those Saturdays a few years ago. A mechanical engineering student who lied to his friends he was attending cooking classes, when in fact he would take a long bus ride every day after a long day at school to attend a dance academy, so that he can improve his skills. And then one Saturday, he waited in line like hundreds of other hopeful young people, but he went inside and impressed Loo Sooman enough to get picked as a SM trainee straight away. This is something that only eight SM idols in the history of SM Ent. have managed to do- Heechul, Yoona, Yeri, Taemin, Seulgi, Haechan, Giselle, and of course Jungwoo. These idols are aces and were picked by Lee Sooman himself, so please do not underestimate Jungwoo. He is a man of so many talents. If you bias him, you will get to know that, cause SM for some reason isn't letting him show it off openly, but maybe that's what they want, who knows? I just hope they give him more chances to showcase his beautiful vocals like in this video. He truly has so so much to show the world<3
